4.5/5  rDev +1.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Adding a review after the '15 I had recently. Opened at room temperature.
L: Wonderful deep red hue with a slightly pink head. Great carb.
S: Smells like funk wine! I feel like the fruited Cantillons just work with their signature funk better than their Gueuze. It's very clean.
T: It is very similar to a carbonated wine with some clean funk. Since this is a '15, it's definitely very fruit forward and jammy.
O: Probably my favorite vintage yet. Saint Lam has always been one of my least favorite Cantillon fruits, but I really enjoyed this bottle. 554 characterscultclassic89, Dec 28, 2014
