4.42/5  rDev -0.2%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4Got a glass of this on draft during Puckerfest at Belmont Station. Served in a tulip glass, the body is a pretty orange color with rose highlights, topped by a wispy, thin, creamy layer of head. Aroma of wine grapes, peach, some general tropical fruit notes, and a good dose of sour, all with an underlying layer of booze.
